Two paired fixes for the 2026-04-30 SME panel query
"¿Cuáles son las fechas límite ... NIT? ¿Dónde encuentro el decreto de
plazos vigente y qué consecuencias tiene la presentación extemporánea?"

Phase 1 — Truncated chunk-tail filter (L13).
The cloud Supabase chunk for art. 641 ends literally at "...por cada mes
o fra" with no trailing punctuation. The splitter at
`_evidence_candidate_lines` then auto-appended a period producing a
170-char "sentence" ending in `fra.` which passed the 45-240 length
filter and reached the renderer as a visibly truncated bullet.
Companion fix for the related stray-punctuation-mid-word case (`fra.`,
`fra:`, `fra;` followed by `ción`) via `_merge_abbreviation_splits`.
Both regexes share `_ABBREVIATION_TOKENS` so synonyms grow in one
place. Adds `_TRUNCATED_TAIL_TOKEN_RE` end-tail check before the
auto-period decision.

Phase 2 — Canonical question shapes (L14).
Sub-Q "¿Cuáles son las fechas límite ... NIT?" was correctly classified
by keyword fallback as `declaracion_renta` but `fix_v5_phase6b:
subquery_inherited_parent` overrode it with the parent's
`regimen_sancionatorio_extemporaneidad` (because "extemporánea" appears
only in sub-Q #1). The straightforward rollback would re-break last
week's +3-strong win. Instead: a config-driven canonical-shape table
that fires BEFORE the parent-inheritance check. When a shape matches,
the keyword-fallback result is promoted to `mode=canonical_shape`
(confidence 0.9), which the inheritance branch leaves alone (it only
fires on `mode=fallback`). Last week's win stays intact for everything
the table doesn't explicitly cover.

Companion: `compatible_doc_topics.json` adjacency wiring. Routing alone
isn't enough — the answer's source document
(`seccion-06-calendario-tributario.md`) carries
`topic_key=calendario_obligaciones`, so the L3 5-signal classifier
needs a compat entry to promote it to primary under `declaracion_renta`
queries. Adds three mutual-compat entries:
declaracion_renta ↔ calendario_obligaciones ↔ regimen_sancionatorio_extemporaneidad.

